Data wrangling with dplyr

Today’s practical is all about how to manipulate data using dplyr

We’re going to be working through a lot of problems. If you struggle with them, then don’t worry. You can also come back to these problems are your confidence builds. With some practise you’ll start to find the problems easier.

To access the problems, I’ve made an RMarkdown document for you to work through. You’ll just been filling in the code chunks to complete the problems. All the problems have example output. Take a look at the example output to help you work through the problem. Try things out, see what happens, and eventually you’ll get it right!

Good luck!
